{
  "stem": "13469.6",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We cooked the raw potatoes, and the grass, and anything else that we could find in the fields.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we cooked it there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we definitely know we were on a passenger coach.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it might have been a mixed train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were also-- there were SS guards on the train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But they didn't really bother us too much, because they were-- they could see that it was getting to the end.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they were more worried about their own future, I think, than they were worried about us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But there was an anti-aircraft gun, or some kind of military equipment at the back of our train.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So despite the fact that we put white flags out, and we put big white sheets on top of the train, the train was often attacked by Allied planes.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I particularly remember one day that we were attacked by fighter planes with twin fuselage-- very distinctive type of fighter planes.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I found out after the war that these were P-38 Lightnings-- American planes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they attacked our plane.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we would all get out of the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We would all lie in the fields, and we would watch.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was great fun, in a way, to see these planes diving down and shooting at the train and starting the odd fire.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But they never actually disabled the train entirely, so we always managed to move on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But this business about getting out of the train, which the SS didn't stop us, started us-- whilst we were lying in the fields, we were taking the grass and cabbage, or any kinds of greens that we could see, and the potatoes.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We would dig them out of the field, and we'd take them back to the train.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
